{{unref|date=July 2018}}
'''Endaural phenomena''' are [[sound]]s that are [[hearing (sense)|heard]] without any external [[acoustics|acoustic]] stimulation. Endaural means "in the [[ear]]". Phenomena include transient [[ringing (medicine)|ringing]] in the ears (that sound like [[sine tones]]), [[white noise]]-like sounds, and subjective [[tinnitus]]. Endaural phenomena need to be distinguished from [[otoacoustic emission]]s, in which a person's ear emits sounds. The emitter typically cannot hear the sounds made by his or her ear. Endaural phenomena also need to be distinguished from [[sound|auditory]] [[hallucination]]s, which are sometimes associated with [[psychosis]].

