The '''Iwaidjan''' or '''Yiwaidjan languages''' are a small [[language families|family]] of [[non-Pama–Nyungan]] [[Australian Aboriginal languages]] spoken in the [[Cobourg Peninsula]] region of Western [[Arnhem Land]].

In 1997 [[Nicholas Evans (linguist)|Nicholas Evans]] proposed an [[Arnhem Land languages|Arnhem Land family]] that includes the Iwaidjan languages, though their inclusion is not accepted in Bowern (2011).<ref>Bowern, Claire. 2011. ''[http://anggarrgoon.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/austlangs-masterlanguagelist-dec2011.xlsx How Many Languages Were Spoken in Australia?]''</ref>

